article.headline: Marquette holds off Alabama-Birmingham
article.linkText: No. 11 Marquette secures C-USA American title
article.story:
MILWAUKEE (Ticker) -- Dwyane Wade scored 26 points and Robert 
Jackson added 22 as No. 11 Marquette clinched the outright
Conference USA American Division title with a 98-87 victory over
Alabama-Birmingham.

Travis Diener contributed 14 points for the Golden Eagles (22-4,
13-2 C-USA American), who have won four straight games and 14
of the last 15.

Morris Finley poured in 31 points, but the Blazers (16-9, 8-6
National) had their three-game winning streak stopped.

The Golden Eagles can clinch the overall C-USA regular-season
title by winning their finale next Saturday against Cincinnati.
